commit_message:
Generate JSON

Generate JSON data so that tools can easily make use of the info
that reviewday generates.

A new reviewday.json file is generated that has data like

  {
    "generated": "2014-01-03 22:22:33",
    "projects": {
      "identity-api": {
        "https://review.openstack.org/#change,62961": {
          "owner": "Dolph Mathews",
          "score": 48,
          "cause": "No link",
          "feedback": {
            "lowest": 1,
            "highest": 1
          },
          "subject": "cleanup query_string documentation"
        }, ... (for each review uri)
      }, ... (for each project)
    }
  }

Change-Id: Idabafdadb3237410fa866c78d429cf46317fb3fe

Validate name during v2 zone create

The name in the v2 zone create is now being checked to see if it is
a valid domain name format.  Previously you could create a zone
with a name like below
{
  "zone" : {
    "name" : "com.com...........",
    "email" : "hs@rs.com"
  }
}

Closes-Bug: #1271665

Change-Id: Ie2481aec5f4a033df64767dfbff30e56e3133e1c

Fix add role api - bad json keyword

The json body of the add role api, included a typo mistake. The
keyword `roles` should have been `role`. Hence the patch.

$ curl -s -H "Content-Type: application/json" -H "X-Auth-Token: $TOKEN" http://localhost:5000/v3/roles -d '{"roles": {"name": "NewRole"}}' | jq .
{
  "error": {
    "title": "Bad Request",
    "code": 400,
    "message": "create_role() got an unexpected keyword argument 'roles'"
  }
}
$ curl -s -H "Content-Type: application/json" -H "X-Auth-Token: $TOKEN" http://localhost:5000/v3/roles -d '{"role": {"name": "NewRole"}}' | jq .
{
  "role": {
    "name": "NewRole",
    "links": {
      "self": "http://85.233.197.43:5000/v3/roles/a9420a5dedd54197b69e37b4b8fdd737"
    },
    "id": "a9420a5dedd54197b69e37b4b8fdd737"
  }
}

Change-Id: I825d0925114d79d26ae7c43727fc9c9f49171442
